90+2 GOAL 5-3 Jess King puts the result beyond doubt, racing through and poking the ball just beyond Cox's outstretched hands #oufc
89 Another cracking save from Cox to deny Jess King at point-blank range - the offside flag was up anyway 4-3
85 Hannah Cox palms away Emily Hollinshead's close-range shot as Everton use the extra space to open United up 4-3
81 Rosie Lane hobbles off for treatment on an ankle injury and will be able to play no further part. United down to 10 players

72 SUB: Destiney Toussaint limps off after a crunching challenge, to be replaced by Lindsay Pinker
67 Jess King gets on the end of a floated cross but can't guide it on target at the front post 3-3
65 GOOOOAAAAALLLLLL KAYLEIGH HINES AGAIN! Another corner finds Hines unmarked to head home the equaliser! 3-3 #oufc
64 Lauren Allison dances through a couple of challenges before squaring to Holly Pickett, whose shot is turned behind for a corner
63 SUB for United: Danielle Scanlon makes way for Sophie Baker

52 GOOOOAAAAAALLLL!!!! 2-2 Hines won't be denied for long as from the resulting corner she volleys home at the back post! #oufc

Off we got for the second half, United looking to close a 2-1 deficit

44 GOAL 2-1 Chantelle Boye-Hlorkah fires home the rebound after goalkeeper Demi Lambourne had blocked Jess King's header #oufc
38 More good work from Allison and this time her cross finds Destiney Toussaint, who nods it wide 1-1
36 Lauren Allison crosses from the bye line for the lurking Kayleigh Hines to head over 1-1
27 Another excellent save from Lambourne to hold onto Danielle Turner's header at the back post 1-1
25 Demi Lambourne spills a high ball following a collision with Boye-Hlorkah, who then pokes the loose ball wide 1-1
22 Chantelle Boye-Hlarka skips past the challenge of Holly Pickett fires a low drive just wide 1-1
A slight interruption in play as referee Mark Doherty clatters into Danielle Scanlon and sends her sprawling!
10 GOAL 1-1 Simone Magill levels for the hosts with a simple tap-in as Everton break quickly #oufc
9 Great save from Demi Lambourne to keep out a powerful header from Ellie Stweart after she's left unmarked at a corner 0-1
8 A nervy moment in the United area as a ball across is allowed to bounce, but Kayleigh Hines is able to scramble it clear 0-1

FT 2-3 Lauren Allison's late header makes it a Sunday double for United with victory at Millwall #oufc
Into stoppage time now. United are hanging on in the face of some serious pressure. Still 3-2 ahead
86 Kayleigh Hines stoops to head Katie Stanley's cross goalwards but it's blocked on the line. A full-on scramble ensues but the hosts clear
83 Low drive from Katie Stanley forces a low save from Quantrill. United doing all the pursuing at the moment 2-3
79 GOOOOOAAAAALLLLLL!!!!! 2-3 Lauren Allison heads United back into the lead from Kayleigh Hines' lofted free kick #oufc
78 Powerful Kayleigh Hines header cleared on the line following Katie Stanley's corner 2-2
70 Double change for United. Off come Holly Pickett and Isi Meade for Laura Nichol and Ella Franklin-Fraiture
68 Great point-blank save from Sarah Quantrill to deny Lauren Allison in front of goal 2-2
65 Great vision from Hines to pick out Allison's excellent run, but her first touch takes her wide and she shoots into the side netting 2-2
64 SUB: Rosie Lane comes off to be replaced by Madison Lee
61 GOOOOAAAAALLLLL!!! 2-2! There's the equaliser, as Kat Nutman races onto a delightful through ball and side-foots home #oufc
60 Fierce strike from Lauren Allison after a long throw-in. It looked destined for goal but strikes a Millwall defender's face
59 Babjide Rinsola escapes the offside trap and races clear, but fails to find the target under pressure from the retreating Rosie Lane 2-1
57 Lillie Maple has a go with a 25-yard free-kick, which loops high in the air. It takes a fierce dip but not enough to drop below the bar
56 Demi Lambourne gets down well to save from Ashlee Hincks as the hosts break quickly 2-1
51 Kayleigh Hines carves through the Millwall defence but her low left-footed drive lacks power and is well saved 2-1
48 GOAL 2-1 Babajide Rinsola cuts inside from the right and curls a shot into the left-hand corner #oufc
Here we go for the second half. 1-1 at present as Oxford look to restore their lead
HT 1-1 Destiney Toussaint fired United into an early lead, but the U's were pegged back shortly before the half after conceding a penalty
43 Scuffed close-range shot from Lauren Allison draws a scrambled save from Millwall GK Sarah Quantrill 1-1
39 Now Kat Nutman hits the post! A well-struck shot from 16 yards slips past the keeper, but can't beat the upright 1-1
37 PENALTY to Millwall following a trip in the area. Lillie Maple fires it straight down the middle and into the back of the net 1-1 #oufc
37 Ashlee Hincks goes dangerously close to an equaliser, swerving in a shot which cannons back off the crossbar 0-1
32 Kat Nutman goes down injured after a scrambled in the United area, sticking out a leg to poke it clear 0-1
26 So close! Destiney Toussaint almost doubles her tally, smashing an effort off the bar after getting the wrong side 0-1
20 Another chance for the U's as Kayleigh Hines curls in a free-kick, which is easily plucked out of the air by the Millwall keeper 0-1
16 GOOOOOOAAAALLLLL 0-1! Destiney Toussaint gives Oxford the lead tapping in after a good run from Lauren Allison #oufc
9 Millwall keeper Sarah Quantrill again forced into a save, getting down low to block another Toussaint effort 0-0
8 Kayleigh Hines shoots from the edge of the area, but she's off balance and it balloons over the bar 0-0
6 Destiney Toussaint escapes her marker on the right wing and forces the first save of the game with a smart shot 0-0
We're underway at Millwall, with United looking to kick-off their four-match away run with a victory
